<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="expense-n">expense <strong><em>n</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /ɪk'spens/    美 /ɪk'spens/  </p>
<p>[C] &amp; [U]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>支出；费用；代价：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>spare no expense</strong> 
不惜一切代价</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>cut down on one's expenses
节省开支</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>living / household</strong> expenses 
生活费用/家庭开支</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>cover one's daily expenses
应付日常开支</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Running a car is a big expense. 
养一辆车开销很大。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I don't think we can afford the expense.
我认为我们负担不起这个费用。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="at-sbs-expense">at sb's expense</h3>
<p>1.<strong>由某人付费 / 负担费用：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I published a book at my own expense. 
我自费出版了一本书。</p></div>

<h3 id="at-the-expense-of">at the expense of</h3>
<p>1.<strong>以…为代价：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He finished the job at the expense of his health. 
他以健康为代价完成了这项工作。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>One thousand dollars a month is not a fortune but would help cover my living <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (开支).  （2007 天津改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. expenses  </p></div>